013package org.apache.juneau.rest.annotation;
014
015/**
016 * Dummy class that indicates that serializers, parsers, or transforms for a Java class or method should not be inherited.
017 *
018 * <h5 class='section'>Example:</h5>
019 * <p class='bjava'>
020 *    <ja>@RestOp</ja>(
021 *
022 *       <jc>// No serializers are defined method or inherited from the class.</jc>
023 *       serializers=None.<jk>class</jk>,
024 *
025 *       <jc>// No parsers are defined method or inherited from the class.</jc>
026 *       parsers=None.<jk>class</jk>,
027 *
028 *       <jc>// No bean filters are defined method or inherited from the class.</jc>
029 *       beanFilters=None.<jk>class</jk>,
030 *
031 *       <jc>// No POJO swaps are defined method or inherited from the class.</jc>
032 *       swaps=None.<jk>class</jk>
033 *    )
034 * </p>
035 *
036 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
037 * </ul>
038 */
039public final class None {}
